a16n (short for "agent customization") is a toolkit for translating AI agent configuration files between different tools' formats.

üîÑ Bidirectional conversion between Cursor and Claude formats Does its best to warn & inform you about lossy or impossible conversions üìù Preserves metadata including file-specific rules and ignore patterns üéØ CLI tool for easy integration into workflows üß© Plugin architecture for extensibility üîç Type-safe with full TypeScript support

Install via npm: npm install -g a16n Convert Cursor rules to Claude format: a16n cursor-to-claude --source .cursor --target ./ Convert Claude rules to Cursor format: a16n claude-to-cursor --source ./CLAUDE.md --target .cursor
Explore the CLI documentation to learn about available commands Read about the architecture to understand the plugin system
This project is open source. Contributions are welcome! Visit our GitHub repository to get started.
The a16n CLI provides command-line tools for converting AI agent configuration files between Cursor and Claude formats.
Convert Cursor IDE configuration to Claude Code format: a16n cursor-to-claude --source .cursor --target ./
Convert Claude Code configuration to Cursor IDE format: a16n claude-to-cursor --source ./CLAUDE.md --target .cursor

The @a16njs/plugin-claude package implements the Claude Code format plugin for reading and writing CLAUDE.md files and .claude/settings.json ignore patterns.

This plugin handles: Discovering Claude configuration files (CLAUDE.md) Parsing Claude markdown format and metadata Extracting ignore patterns from .claude/settings.json Emitting converted configurations back to Claude format
‚úÖ Nested CLAUDE.md files (directory hierarchy) ‚úÖ Ignore patterns via .claude/settings.json ‚úÖ Markdown section-based rule organization
